Spatial Analysis Portfolio

Sue Chen

Fall 2021

To demonstrate the skillsets I developed in VIS 2128, I have applied each of the skillsets to a Canadian context.

This portfolio demonstrates the following skills: * Displaying multiple vector layers on the same map (see Maps # [add hyperlink]) * Calculating and displaying relationships among point and polygon layers based on distance (see Maps # [add hyperlink]) * Aggregating point data to a layer of polygons (see Maps # [add hyperlink]) * Calculating and displaying accessibility, based on travel time (see Maps # [add hyperlink]) * Converting between raster layers and vector layers (see Maps # [add hyperlink]) * Displaying raster data on a map (see Maps # [add hyperlink]) * Georeferencing a raster image (see Maps # [add hyperlink]) * Displaying data on an interactive map (see Maps # [add hyperlink])
